      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Here is where Flykube gets interesting. You choose a price tier, and that tier determines the quality of your hotel and the range of possible destinations.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Lower tiers mean closer destinations and comfortable-but-modest hotels. Higher tiers unlock farther cities, boutique hotels, and occasionally upgraded perks.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "The pricing is transparent. What you see is what you pay — flights and hotel bundled. There are no hidden booking fees that magically appear at checkout. I have tested this personally, and the final price matched the quoted price every time.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "This budget-first approach is genuinely refreshing. Instead of falling in love with a €800 hotel in Santorini and then wincing, you decide what you want to spend and Flykube builds the best possible trip around that number.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [
